    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4ad9a6af_c089c4f1",
        "filename": "kube/go/pushk/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 19
      },
      "lineNbr": 234,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-12-11T15:50:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This suggestion was primarily for the \"make these changes on master, kubectl apply, and git push\" case, in which you\u0027d want to avoid clobbering developer changes while ensuring that you\u0027re starting from a clean checkout but also avoid failing and forcing the developer to take manual action.  So the developer would never actually see this temporary checkout.  For dry run, you\u0027d definitely want to make the changes to the developer\u0027s directory and not in a temp dir (which you\u0027d have to remember to intentionally leak and log the location of).\n\nAt any rate, because we respect the PUSHK_GITDIR environment variable, this could be done in a wrapper script.  It is a handy property of the autoroll push-helper though, nice to have built in.",
      "parentUuid": "6b3d7a51_2de8e9b9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 234,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 234,
        "endChar": 72
      },
      "revId": "954a3c8e54dca3e1f13da3c5be585ffb23553f94",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e54a9f6a_465034e7",
        "filename": "kube/go/pushk/main.go",
        "patchSetId": 19
      },
      "lineNbr": 239,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-12-11T13:18:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is not sufficient to detect a dirty checkout, eg. if I\u0027ve made changes and committed (but not pushed) them.  In order to share a persistent checkout with a developer, we need to be extra careful not to clobber their changes while also ensuring that we start from an absolutely clean state.  I think the simplest solution is to avoid the problem altogether and a temporary checkout.  Otherwise we\u0027ll need to do some combination of \"git diff origin/master\" (without \"git fetch\") and \"git ls-files --others --exclude-standard\".",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 239,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 239,
        "endChar": 49
      },
      "revId": "954a3c8e54dca3e1f13da3c5be585ffb23553f94",
